===Definitions===

'''iron''' ([[en:Iron|Wikipedia:Iron]])

#A [[metal]]lic chemical [[element]] having [[atomic number]] 26, and symbol Fe. 
#A [[tool]] or [[appliance]] made of iron or other [[metal]], which is [[heat]]ed and then used to [[transfer]] heat to something else, as:
##A [[thick]] [[piece]] of metal fitted with a [[handle]] and having a [[flat]], [[triangular]] [[bottom]], which is heated and used to [[press]] [[wrinkle]]s from [[clothing]], and now usually containing an [[electrical]] heating [[apparatus]].  Formerly called a '''[[flatiron]]'''.
##'''Branding iron'''.  A piece of metal [[bend|bent]] into a [[distinctive]] [[shape]], which is heated and used to [[brand]] [[livestock]].
##'''Curling iron'''.  A metal [[cylinder]] heated and used to [[curl]] [[hair]], now usually containing an electrical heating apparatus.
##'''Waffle iron'''.  A [[pair]] of metal [[plate]]s, usually [[hinge]]d together, having a [[grid]]ded [[surface]] and used for [[bake|baking]] [[waffle]]s.
##'''Soldering iron'''.  A metal tool, now usually electrical, having a [[metal]] [[point]], used to heat [[solder]].
#'''Tire iron'''.  A metal tool used to [[change]] [[tire]]s on a [[car]] or other [[vehicle]].
#'''Irons''' ''([[plural]])''.  [[Shackle]]s.

